	GLFW can tell you the *character* for any key scancode
	according to the current keyboard layout. This is very
	good for the purposes of a remapping interface.
	But anything that doesn't produce a printable character
	returns null, so for example the scancode for the left
	arrow key ends up as "".
	Therefore, this list works as a fallback. None of these
	keys are affected by layout changes anyway.
